    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "inspiration",
        "label": "Inspiration",
        "body": "[Dummy copy] Built late one night after losing a Stunt Park lobby in something far less subtle, this one was about proving restraint could still look mean. The olive and gold were picked to feel like a getaway car that's already won the chase before it started — quiet until it isn't."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "notes",
        "label": "Design Notes",
        "body": "Confirmed via the Forza Wiki: it's the 2007 Formula Drift #117 599 GTB Fiorano — nicknamed \"Fiorella\" — built by Federico Sceriffo, with twin positive-displacement superchargers (not turbos) pushing the V12 to roughly 917 hp, a Hollinger 6-speed sequential replacing the stock semi-automatic F1 transmission, Öhlins coilovers, and at 3,208 lb it's the heaviest car in Formula Drift's Forza roster. Front-mid-engine layout gives it a rear-biased 47/53 weight split; custom control arms and wide fenders were fitted specifically to increase steering angle — the whole point of the car."
      },
