    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "inspiration",
        "label": "Inspiration",
        "body": "Lolita is set up with rally tires and suspension. I'll have to get back to you on the tuning, as that's a next-tier initiative to include specific tunings that go with the cars. But the idea with this setup is that it can do most everything. It can drift pretty well — rally tires are, in my opinion, the second-best for drifting — and obviously they give improved speed and traction on the dirt road speed zones. Basically, it's a pretty good car to do Stunt Party and many of the PR Events. It's not the fastest possible, but it definitely will test your limits of control."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "notes",
        "label": "Design Notes",
        "body": "Built on the Mazda MX-5 Miata Forza Edition shell — stock, that's a V10-swapped drag special. Lolita's been pulled in a completely different direction: converted to AWD, dropped onto rally rubber. The damascus-steel wrap reads almost like a topographic map at a glance, which is exactly why it took a second look to realize it wasn't one — the rippling forge-pattern and contour lines share that same swirling logic."
      },
      {
