        "label": "Inspiration",
        "body": "[Dummy copy] Started as a joke about how serious every other build in this catalog had gotten. The smiley face was supposed to be temporary — a placeholder livery for a single screenshot — and then it just never came off, because something about a trophy truck grinning through a mountain pass was funnier every time it got photographed again."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "notes",
        "label": "Design Notes",
        "body": "[Dummy copy] The smiley itself is a built-in decal, not hand-painted, scaled up to cover most of the rear quarter panel. The challenge was less the face and more keeping the rest of the livery quiet enough that the one goofy element actually reads as the point rather than competing with anything else going on."
      },
