    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "inspiration",
        "label": "Inspiration",
        "body": "Although B.A. Baracus famously feared flying, this van can catch plenty of air and look badass doin' it! Upgraded carbon fiber body and authentic bullet holes in the rear panel — you'll have plenty of muscle to get away from the bad guys, and with that mean stance, you'll look like you're going a hundred miles an hour standing still.",
        "figurePath": "/uploads/6-inspiration.jpg"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "key": "notes",
        "label": "Design Notes",
        "body": "Built on the GMC Vandura shell as a direct callback to the actual A-Team van, but pushed further than the show ever did: the roof gets a carbon-fiber texture instead of plain sheet metal, the red pinstripe is sharpened into a single clean diagonal rather than the original's slightly softer line, and the wheels are swapped to a red-lipped aftermarket style instead of the steelies the real van wore. The rear panel carries \"Pity the fool\" in script — a Mr. T line that never actually appeared on the van itself, added here as the kind of detail a fan would want but the show never gave them."
      },
      {
        "type": "forza_recipe",
        "key": "recipe",
        "label": "Tune / Build Parts",
        "tuneName": "A-Team (10-Spd)",
        "shareCode": "TBD",
